==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irresolvable
<hw>Ir`re*solv"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>ir-</ets> not + <ets>resolvable</ets>. Cf.
<er>Irresoluble</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being resolved; not
separable into component parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Irresolvable nebul⟦ae⟧</b></col> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>,
<cd>nebul⟦ae⟧ of a cloudlike appearance, which have not yet been
resolved by the telescope into stars, and are often distant galaxies.
See <er>galaxy</er>{2}.</cd></cs> <rj><au>Sir W. Herschel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irresolvableness</ent>⟦br⟧
